As of the census of 2010, there were 165 people and 127 housing units in the [[Census-designated place|CDP]].  The CDP was a new CDP created in the 2010 census.  The population density was 237.5 people per square mile.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>  Prior to the 2010 census, the San Simon area was only a part of the much larger [[Bowie, Arizona|Bowie]] [[Census county division|CCD]] for census purposes.
